# Graphical Representation tools

#[1] plot()	Creates line plots with customizable styles.
#[2] scatter()	Generates scatter plots to visualize relationships.
#[3] bar()	Creates bar charts for comparing categories.
#[4] hist()	Draws histograms to show data distribution.
#[5] pie()	Creates pie charts to represent parts of a whole.
#[6] xlabel(), ylabel()	Sets labels for the X and Y axes.
#[7] title()	Adds a title to the plot.
#[8] legend()	Adds a legend to differentiate data series.
#[9] xlim(), ylim()	Sets limits for the X and Y axes.
#[10] grid()	Adds gridlines to the plot for readability.
#[11] show()	Displays the plot in a window.
#[12] figure()	Creates or activates a figure.
#[13] subplot()	Creates a grid of subplots within a figure.
#[14] savefig()	Saves the current figure to a file.